Colombo Stock Exchange Halts Trading After ‘Hardware Breakdown’

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-09-19T06:42:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/colombo-stock-exchange-halts-trading-after-hardware-breakdown-.html
Trading on  Sri Lanka ’s  Colombo
Stock Exchange  was halted today after a “hardware breakdown,”
Chief Executive Officer Surekha Sellahewa said in a telephone
interview today.  It may take another two hours for the “system to be
restored,” she said, without elaborating.  The benchmark Colombo All Share Index last traded at
6,886.88, up 0.2 percent, at 9:34 a.m., according to exchange
data.  Link to Company News: {JKH SL <Equity> CN}  To contact the reporter on this story:
